  "name": "Schizophrenia - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying schizophrenia patients via Condition + MedicationRequest. Path C captures patients on antipsychotics without coded schizophrenia dx (typically bipolar mania, MDD adjunct, dementia agitation).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete schizophrenia patient population for a behavioral health quality initiative. Some patients have a coded schizophrenia diagnosis. Others are on antipsychotics without ever getting a formal schizophrenia diagnosis — typically these are bipolar mania, depression with psychotic features, or dementia-related behavioral symptoms. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and antipsychotic medications — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all schizophrenia patients.",
    "broad": "Find all schizophrenia patients — by diagnosis or by antipsychotic medications. Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|58214004 — schizophrenia dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|5093,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|35636,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|61381,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|51272 — antipsychotics. Union the patient IDs."
  },
